%% 04-ralph-state-machine.mmd â€” Ralph orchestrator (scripts/ralph.py)
%% Resumable plannerâ†’executorâ†’reviewerâ†’re-reviewer loop driven by a manifest.
%% The per-iteration phase advances strictly leftâ†’right; death/kill parks the
%% iteration at its current phase and `resume`/supervisor re-launches the runner.
%% CLI entry: ,ralph (home/exact_bin/executable_,ralph) â†’ scripts/ralph.py
%% ============================================================================
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> planning : ralph go --goal
    [*] --> executing : ralph go --spec (operator spec, planner skipped)

    planning --> awaiting_human : role emits RALPH_QUESTIONS (status=awaiting_human)
    awaiting_human --> replanning : ,ralph answer (sets replan_requested)

    planning --> executing : plan accepted (iteration starts)

    state "per-iteration loop" as ITER {
        direction LR
        executing --> reviewing : exec done + criteria checks machine-run
        reviewing --> rereviewing : reviewer verdict (feature/bugfix)
        rereviewing --> decided : re-reviewer verdict (unparseable â†’ needs_iteration)
        reviewing --> decided : review/research workflow (no re-reviewer)
    }

    decided --> replanning : verdict=fail & iters<max
    replanning --> executing : next iteration
    decided --> done : verdict=pass & all criteria checks green
    decided --> executing : verdict=pass over failing check â†’ needs_iteration
    decided --> failed : max_iterations / max_minutes exceeded
    decided --> blocked : verdict=block (status=needs_human, phase=blocked)
    blocked --> executing : ,ralph resume (next same-plan iteration)

    done --> reflecting : workflow in {feature,bugfix} & reflector_enabled
    reflecting --> [*] : capsule â†’ AI KB
    done --> [*]
    failed --> [*]

    note right of executing
        Control overlay (ralph control --action):
        takeoverâ†’manual_control Â· dirtyâ†’dirty_control
        resumeâ†’resume_requested Â· autoâ†’automated
        BLOCKING states pause the runner until cleared.

        Eligible material prose â†’ text-tournament Ralph lane:
        executor generates 3 candidates + TOURNAMENT, then the
        existing reviewer/re-reviewer evaluate; no new phase/judge.
    end note

    note right of blocked
        Reviewer/re_reviewer BLOCK park: status=needs_human, phase=blocked,
        block_reason set, NO role control. Cleared ONLY by ,ralph resume
        (starts the next same-plan iteration; spec_seq unchanged).
        verify / direct runner / supervisor keep it parked; ,ralph replan rejects it.
    end note

    note right of planning
        Config: ~/.config/ralph/roles.json (planner/executor/
        reviewer/re_reviewer/reflector â†’ harness+model+extra_args).
        Prompts: dot_config/ralph/prompts/{planner,executor,reviewer,
        re_reviewer,reflector}.md.
        planner/reviewer = cursor --mode plan/ask; executor = --force.
        re_reviewer DIVERSITY GATE: family != reviewer family
        {claude,gpt,gemini,llama,mistral,deepseek}.
    end note
